        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I added the following line to config file\r\n\r\n```\r\nlet &shellcmdflag='-c'\r\n```\r\n\r\nNow `:!pwd` works but `:!cargo b` doesn't. \r\n\r\n```\r\n:!cargo b\r\n/usr/bin/bash: line 1: cargo b: command not found\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt is somehow passing `cargo b` as a single word to shell. `:!\"cargo b\"` works as expected. ",
